For the files for episodes 11 to 25, the aspect ratio flag is set to 4:3. But it should have been set to 16:9. So view these videos with the aspect ratio overridden to 16:9.

Thanks to the original cappers.

Please DO NOT IMMEDIATELY REMOVE this from your client's torrent list! Leave it seeding in your client's torrent list for at least a few days to help other people get a copy who may seed it long term. Please show some good will to others. And a tiny bit of courage. You will have already provided others with pieces of the torrent while you were downloading anyway. If you are afraid to seed, get a VPN (one proper for P2P that forwards incoming ports).

Be sure you have DHT, Peer Exchange, Local Peer Discovery enabled in your client. Many people (like me) use VPN-s or seedboxes now and the main open public trackers (like OpenBittorrent and PublicBT, which TPB and others add to torrents) block them. So you may not find me/us without this.

